            "summary": "On April 15, 2025, Associated Builders and Contractors released data showing that the Construction Backlog Indicator reached 8.5 months in March, based on a survey of ABC members conducted from March 20 to April 6. This marks a 0.3 month increase compared to March 2024. The report indicates a growth in backlog for all nonresidential subsegments on a monthly basis in March, with infrastructure showing the most significant backlog increase over the past year. Additionally, ABC's Construction Confidence Index for staffing saw an improvement. To access the full details, including tables and graphs, visit the ABC website.",
            "source_type": "news",
            "headline": "ABC's Construction Backlog Indicator increased to 8.5 months in March, up 0.3 months from March 2024.Backlog rose in nonresidential subsegments, with significant growth in infrastructure backlog. Staffing confidence improved.",
